We were 5 hours in and only a little time left with nothing to show. I shutdown, I got frustrated (which Fernando, my guitarist caught part of here lol). It was so hard to get this day together - where it was timing, finances, kids having colds, tour schedule…getting into the studio to record these two tracks has been difficult and I wasn’t leaving without at least something. Each person I picked to be apart of this session for a reason and I let them know that were here to make classics not just another release but up there the best Instrumental and  Chicano records ever. Up there with my heroes Santana, Jean Luc Ponty, Charlie Daniels, Miles Davis, Herbie Hancock, Dave Brubeck but not by copying them, by being original and ourselves we’ll prove it. WE’RE FROM FRESNO LETS PLAY LIKE IT. And guess what, we Delivered JUST in time … man did we deliver. I can’t wait for you to hear. 

Listen to Tijuana & Cholo Pants on my new album releasing in May.

This represents decades of training and work on my musicianship, some songs are co-written others are just me - All are personal and have a story. I already have a band put together and we’ve started working to be ready to debut my music March 3 a @thesirenmorrobay in Morro Bay. The sound is a mix of Latin / Pop / R&B / Rock some of my major influences are George Benson, Carlos Santana, Gipsy Kings. You can hear some of these on my album A Little Night Music streaming on all major platforms. 

I’m bringing the best musicians I know to join me on stage and were gonna have a huge encore jam set blowout as well. March 3 The Siren, a new chapter starts. Come be apart!

I’m still booking weddings, I’m gonna be still playing fairs solo, I love them and it affords me to be an independent recording artist. In the meantime, I’ll slowly start to do shows under my name with a full band playing my own music, and perhaps a special encore of santana but being careful not to take away the shine of my own story and music. Santana’s music is already proven, now it’s my turn. After that it’s really up to the support of the fans but my heart is so sure that even if I only had 10 listeners that really got it I’d be happy.

I hope to see you March 3 at @thesirenmorrobay for the start of this new journey 🎻🎻🎻

I was dreading posting this. I have to reschedule my album release and push back the date which I will announce when I’m sure I can stick with it. I’m sorry guys, I was doing all I could to finish up the record but my performance schedule has just been too busy. I’ve invested so much in this album I don’t want to sacrifice quality. I found myself in recording sessions exhausted and trying to push through but just not hitting a level you or I deserve for an album. I had been working on two records at the same time and was planning to release one in September and the other in Spring 2024, I’m gonna combine them into one huge record of 20-25 original songs (depending on how many make the cut). I’m working with @reelfonkyproductions & @omarnare on writing and production. Although nothing is a guarantee and it could be a flop that interests no one, I have the feeling we have something special and I want to deliver it right. I will be working to book a show before the end of the year Fresno where I can perform my last record “A Little Night Music” because I’ve only performed it once at The Siren in Morro Bay and man was that a experience (for me, at least… hopefully you too). You can listen that that album here: https://music.apple.com/us/album/a-little-night-music-deluxe-edition/1656161456

In the meantime I’ve been offered to perform Sept 12-17 in Spokane, Wa at Interstate Spokane Fair and I’ve decided to take it. As you know, I’m self funding my own record and need to work as much as I can so I don’t cut any corners in making this record. I work hard and want to make sure that my records are the one place I get to really be me a deliver my sound without sacrificing any vision I have. 

I will be posting up a couple dates in town where I’ll be performing A Little Night Music before the end of the year to make up for this and will be aiming for Warnors Theater in Spring 2024 for a full album release concert which I wanna sell out and will need all your support.. but only if you enjoy the music. Thank you for all your support, it goes without saying but I wouldn’t be here without you.

Update: it seems like Violin On Fire is well, ON FIRE lol. Seriously the amount of inquiries is astounding. I still have 6 fairs left and in November traveling to 4 talent conventions in Salt Lake City, UT .. Laughlin, NV.. Coeur d'Alene, Idaho & finally Anaheim, Ca to meet with agents, talent buyers. My goal is to slowly build toward the East Coast now that I’m establishing Western United States. Little by little, I’m definitely putting in the work, sweat and tears. 

On the merch side:
I ordered a new round of two different cool stickers I had designed and hard copies of my album A Little Night Music to sell at fairs since people are asking for music, along with a album of electric violin covers featuring my band. So there’s the option of both original music and covers. Next up is shirts which I badly need, I’m saving my money for that so I can make sure they are quality. 

Currently I’m in beautiful Bishop, Ca Today through Sunday I’ll be performing strolling sets everyday at @tricountyfairgrounds

No label, no vocals, no PR, a violin record, no covers. To be in there with the big names and budgets is insane to me. We made this record in Sanger not Nashville or any place known for studios. I didn’t leave Fresno, we tried for LA but my schedule got so crazy we stayed here. The record releases tonight at 9pm on all platforms, I’ve done all I can do.. as much as I love to be in control I’m not. This is up to you guys. If you want to support buy the album on Amazon Music, Apple Music or however you stream your music. I have a limited amount of CD’s printed which I will sell at this weekends shows starting off with the siren tomorrow night in Morro Bay. 

If you’ve followed my page you’ve seen the grind. I went out in the sun, rain, heat, cold and played - I played my butt off in every condition never slacking at any fair or show. I pushed forward  slowly saving money putting into the record bit by bit. Keeping this dream tucked away in the corner of my heart. With that said, hard work doesn’t make music good. It just doesn’t. You can work hard and still make terrible music. I won’t be the judge if I make good music, you will. Whatever happens I can look back and know, I gave it my best shot and left nothing on the table.
